    {
      "section_id": "para_39",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "An act to confer jurisdiction upon Courts constituted under any State \nlaw for the purpose of dealing with offences under Islamic law.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_40",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "[1 April 1965]",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_41",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "BE  IT  ENACTED  by  the  Seri  Paduka  Baginda  Yang  di-Pertuan \nAgong with the advice and consent of the Dewan Negara and Dewan \nRakyat in Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as \nfollows:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_42",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Short title and application",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_43",
      "heading": "1.  (1)  This  Act  may  be  cited  as  the  Syariah  Courts  (Criminal \nJurisdiction) Act 1965.",
      "content": "1.  (1)  This  Act  may  be  cited  as  the  Syariah  Courts  (Criminal \nJurisdiction) Act 1965.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_44",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  This Act shall apply to all the States of Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_45",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Criminal Jurisdiction of Syariah Courts",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_46",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "2.   The  Syariah  Courts  duly  constituted  under  any  law  in  a  State \nand invested with jurisdiction over persons professing the religion of \nIslam and in respect of any of the matters enumerated in List II of the \nState  List  of  the  Ninth  Schedule  to  the  Federal  Constitution  are \nhereby  conferred  jurisdiction  in  respect  of  offences  against  precepts \nof the religion of Islam by persons professing that religion which may \nbe prescribed under any written law:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_47",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6                                           Laws of Malaysia                      ACT 355",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_48",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Provided that such jurisdiction shall not be exercised in respect of \nany offence punishable with imprisonment for a term exceeding three \nyears  or  with  any  fine  exceeding  five  thousand  ringgit  or  with \nwhipping exceeding six strokes or with any combination thereof.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_49",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Validation",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_50",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "law  which  before",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_51",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "the \nIslamic \n3.  All  offences  under \ncommencement  of  this  Act  in  relation  to  the  States  of  Peninsular \nMalaysia and which before the commencement of the Syariah Courts \n(Criminal  Jurisdiction)  (Amendment  and  Extension)  Act  1989  in \nrelation to the States of Sabah and Sarawak, had been tried by any of \nthe Courts aforesaid shall be deemed to have been validly tried as if \njurisdiction in respect thereof had been conferred on those Courts by \nFederal law.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
